\section{Background and Related Work}
Survey data indicates that AI-generated video adoption has risen significantly, with average tool usage per film increasing, confirming a multi-tool reality where no single platform provides the full capability stack (Zhang et al., 2025). The dominant paradigm has shifted to diffusion models (e.g., Kling 2.0, Google Veo 3.1), while parallel advances in 3D generation via Neural Radiance Fields (NeRF) and Gaussian Splatting offer spatial consistency capabilities. 

The ASPF imports Virtual Production's core insight --- build the world before you shoot it --- into a generative pipeline at solo-creator cost, addressing critical gaps in existing literature: spatial pre-construction for SVI prevention, closed-loop agentic continuity, audio coherence as an independent dimension, and quantitative metrics for identity drift.

