\section{Conclusion}
Long-form realistic AI filmmaking remains a technically demanding discipline. This paper has identified four principal challenge axes (CID, NTI, SVI, ACD) and documented solution strategies. The proposed Agentic Spatial Production Framework (ASPF) offers a structured alternative to linear pipeline approaches. By integrating 3D spatial pre-construction, closed-loop multi-agent continuity control, and quantitative quality gates (cCID, APDI), the framework shifts the locus of consistency management from post-production remediation toward prevention. While analytical projections suggest significant cost reductions, the field requires instrumented, end-to-end case studies to validate these design targets.

